100 years ago today there was a flood in my hometown of Pueblo, CO. It destroyed the town and you can still see high water marks on some of the buildings still standing today.

My first report in 3rd grade was all about the Pueblo flood of 1921. I remember researching and reading through some picture books at the library. One of the books said that after the flood people began to use motorized vehicles and horses were no longer used. 

I took that to mean that horses went extinct...

So yesterday and today my Dad reminded me of this monumental occasion ü§£ü§£ü§£ü§£

They are NOT re-flooding the streets and horses can still be found ü§£

In this situation, our client was away from their home while a pressure valve to their heating system burst. 

While these floors were considered unsalvageable, depending on the case some hardwood floors can be salvaged by using specialized drying techniques.

Went for a Run to see what damage the flood did to the River tracküòîAbsolutely Devastating!üíîWhat a mess!
Can say we won't be running or Biking these tracks for quite some timeüòî. This was only 1 small section as I could'nt get any further.
This week has been chaos with our Town Bridge also sagging & being closed. My partner got stuck on the town side & could'nt get home on Tuesday frm work. Trucks could'nt get through to bring supplies. Work was crazy (I'm a Baker) Tinwald ran out of Bread since there was no trucks so we had to make crazy amounts of stuff.
I read Mt SomersüåÑWhere I always go is also closed & those tracks badly damaged aswell as the access roadüòî
They say u don't know what u've got until its gone. This is really sad, so much to clean up around the Districtüíî

How to save on your homeowners insurance:
1.) Consider increasing your hurricane and all other claim deductibles 
2.) Maintain a good credit score
3.) Consider a central station fire & burglar alarm as this can sometimes reduce your premium by 10%
4.) Speak to an independent insurance agency as they will have more options with several insurance carriers 

South Shore Insurance is an independent agency and we have many contracts with insurance companies based in Florida and all over the country.
